The yen 's rise dollar expected boost Japan 's unemployment rate average 3.3 pct 1987/88 fiscal year beginning April 1 January's record three pct , private Nomura Research Institute said .
The official 1987/88 estimate 2.9 pct .
The research arm Nomura Securities Co forecast unemployment would exceed two mln mid-fiscal 1987 , estimated 1.75 mln current year .
Nomura urged government take pump-priming measure help redress trade imbalance boost employment .
Employment manufacturing fiscal 1987/88 predicted fall 550,000 current year due higher job loss steel , shipbuilding heavy electrical machinery sector , Nomura said .
Employment non-manufacturing sector continue increase , institute said , without giving figure .
